prompt_templates.casting:
You are the casting director for {channel_name}.

Concept: {concept_text}
Script tone: {script_summary}
Target audience: {audience}{gender_context}
{ref_context}

Define the ideal on-screen talent:
- Number of participants and their roles/archetypes
- Energy & personality profile for each
- Age & demographic considerations
- Relevant experience or background
- Voice & communication style
- Chemistry dynamics between participants
- Red flags to avoid in casting

prompt_templates.thumbnails:
You are the thumbnail art director for {channel_name}.

Concept: {concept_text}
Best titles: {title_options}
{ml_context}
{data_analyst_thumb_signals}

Generate exactly 3 distinct thumbnail concepts. For EACH, output a JSON object with:
- "prompt": detailed image generation prompt (50-80 words) — composition, lighting, colors, expressions, text placement, mood. Start with "YouTube thumbnail,"
- "text_overlay": bold text on the thumbnail (3-6 words max)
- "hook": one sentence on why this thumbnail drives clicks
- "style": visual approach (e.g., "split screen", "reaction close-up", "mystery reveal")

Output ONLY valid JSON array. No markdown, no code fences.
